MY UNDERSTANDING OF THE TASK PRIORITY AND SORTING SYSTEM. 

The feature calculates the importance score for each task using multiple factors then sorts out the tasks using the score 

A list of task 
    |
CalculateTaskScore
    |
Each task is given a score
    |
    sortTaskByImportance()
    |
Task is filtered and sorted from highest score to lowest score
    |
Top task is displayed

in my understanding that each task gets a score made up of multiple parts. Namely base priority, due date, status , tag boost and activity boost

Base Priority(low, medium, high and urgent) - this is the starting point

urgency - task closer to deadlines become more important

status score- tasks that are completed or waiting for a review are oushed to the bottom

Tag Boost - manual urgency increase score

Activity Boost - recently active tasks are semi prioritized

in  my understanding
score = priority + due date factor - status + tag boost + update boost

meanwhile, sorting logic is by score descending. highest score comes first and lowest score comes last

Multiple signals influence priority and not one field. Sorting is also not fixed

